       "  AIMessage(content=\"Recent developments in Supreme Court judgments related to technology include significant rulings that impact the responsibilities of tech companies regarding user-generated content and their liability for harmful actions.\\n\\n1. **Twitter and Google Rulings**: On May 18, 2023, the US Supreme Court ruled in favor of Twitter and Google, reinforcing the limited liability shield that protects platforms from being held responsible for user-generated content. This decision is crucial as it continues to shape the legal landscape for tech companies, allowing them to avoid liability for harmful content posted by users on their platforms. [Read more here](https://equalitynow.org/news/news-and-insights/online-abuse-us-supreme-court-rulings-on-tech-companies-responsibility-to-protect-users-from-harmful-content/).\\n\\n2. **Cisco Systems, Inc. v. Doe**: The Supreme Court also heard oral arguments in a case concerning Cisco Systems, which involves allegations of the company's involvement in human rights abuses in China. This case raises important questions about the extent to which tech companies can be held accountable for their business practices abroad, particularly in relation to human rights violations. [More details can be found here](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wirNXZfgfUc).\\n\\n3. **Landmark Verdicts Against Big Tech**: Recently, there have been landmark verdicts against major tech companies like Meta and YouTube, which held them liable for harms caused by their products. These cases mark a shift in how courts may view the responsibilities of tech companies in relation to user safety and content moderation. [Learn more about these verdicts](https://finance.yahoo.com/sectors/technology/articles/last-week-landmark-verdicts-against-195637571.html).\\n\\nThese rulings reflect an evolving legal framework that seeks to balance the interests of technology companies with the need to protect users from harm.\", additional_kwargs={'refusal': None}, response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 379, 'prompt_tokens': 970, 'total_tokens': 1349, 'completion_tokens_details': {'accepted_prediction_tokens': 0, 'audio_tokens': 0, 'reasoning_tokens': 0, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': 0}, 'prompt_tokens_details': {'audio_tokens': 0, 'cached_tokens': 0}}, 'model_provider': 'openai', 'model_name': 'gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18', 'system_fingerprint': 'fp_b985008419', 'id': 'chatcmpl-DeFpkCzoQ5PusdGt8gqWgh3XEU8d9', 'service_tier': 'default', 'finish_reason': 'stop', 'logprobs': None}, id='lc_run--019e160c-2688-7e23-a4be-a7f3c6805e74-0', tool_calls=[], invalid_tool_calls=[], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 970, 'output_tokens': 379, 'total_tokens': 1349, 'input_token_details': {'audio': 0, 'cache_read': 0}, 'output_token_details': {'audio': 0, 'reasoning': 0}})]}"
